<div id=3D"outline-container-4" class=3D"outline-2">
<h2 id=3D"4">Research engineer or postdoc position at Inria Rennes: static =
analysis of OCaml programs</h2>
<div class=3D"outline-text-2" id=3D"text-4">
<p>
Archive: <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/research-engineer-or-postdo=
c-position-at-inria-rennes-static-analysis-of-ocaml-programs/17879/1">https=
://discuss.ocaml.org/t/research-engineer-or-postdoc-position-at-inria-renne=
s-static-analysis-of-ocaml-programs/17879/1</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orgbb0d6d7" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"orgbb0d6d7">Beno=C3=AEt Montagu announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-orgbb0d6d7">
<p>
Dear OCaml folks,
</p>

<p>
as part of a project between <a href=3D"https://www.inria.fr/">Inria</a> an=
d <a href=3D"https://www.lexifi.com/">Lexifi</a>, we are offering a 2-year =
research engineer or postdoc position, to work on the <a href=3D"https://sa=
lto.gitlabpages.inria.fr/">Salto static analyser</a> for OCaml programs.
The position can start anytime from spring 2026, and is located in the <a h=
ref=3D"https://team.inria.fr/epicure/">=C3=89picure Inria research team</a>=
, in the vibrant city of Rennes, France.
If you have successfully defended a Ph.D. in computer science, and you are =
acquainted with the topic of static analysis, please contact me!
</p>

<p>
Experience with programming in OCaml or in another functional language is s=
trongly recommended.
</p>

<p>
If you want to know more about this position, please have look at the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://jobs.inria.fr/public/classic/en/offres/2026-09842">detailed j=
ob description</a>, and <a href=3D"https://people.irisa.fr/Benoit.Montagu/"=
>contact me</a>!
</p>

<p>
Please feel free to transfer this announce to people that you think could b=
e interested.
</p>
</div>
